value.value: A synthetic agent derivative of pyrimido-pyrimidine, with antiplatelet properties.  Dipyridamole inhibits adenosine uptake by platelets and endothelial cells, triggering an accumulation of cyclic adenosine monophosphate (cAMP), and inhibiting the stimulation of platelet aggregation by agents such as platelet activating factor and collagen. (NCI04)
An undifferentiated non-small cell lung carcinoma composed of large polygonal cells without evidence of glandular, squamous, or neuroendocrine differentiation.

label.value: Lung Large Cell Carcinoma, Clear Cell Variant

value.value: A large cell lung carcinoma characterized by a predominance of clear cells that may or may not contain glycogen.
The use of compounds targeting anatomic structures to enhance radiation cytotoxicity.
A morphologic variant of lung sarcomatoid carcinoma characterized by the presence of mononuclear and multinucleated pleomorphic neoplastic giant cells that lack cohesion.
Part of the chromosome bands present on the long (q) arm of chromosome 18.
Part of the chromosome bands present on the short (p) arm of chromosome 11.

A low-grade malignant blood vessel neoplasm arising from the lung.  It is characterized by the presence of epithelioid endothelial cells.  The neoplastic cells are arranged in cords and nests, which are embedded in a myxoid to hyalinized stroma.
